roomler-agent for Debian/Ubuntu
===============================

First-time setup
----------------

  # 1. Generate an enrollment JWT at http://roomler.ai/ (Admin -> Agents).
  # 2. Enroll this machine (as your normal user, NOT root):
  roomler-agent enroll --server http://roomler.ai/ \
                       --token <paste-enrollment-jwt> \
                       --name "$(hostname)"

  # 3. Run once in the foreground to confirm capture + signalling work.
  #    You need an active X11 session — tty login won't capture anything.
  RUST_LOG=roomler_agent=debug,webrtc=info roomler-agent run

Autostart (systemd --user)
--------------------------

The package ships a systemd user unit at
/usr/lib/systemd/user/roomler-agent.service. Enable it as your own user:

  systemctl --user daemon-reload
  systemctl --user enable --now roomler-agent.service
  systemctl --user status roomler-agent.service

Logs:
  journalctl --user -u roomler-agent.service -f

Disable:
  systemctl --user disable --now roomler-agent.service

Wayland note
------------

The current capture backend (scrap) is X11-only. Under Wayland the agent
will fail at session start. Either log in to an X11 session, or wait for
the PipeWire portal backend (see docs/remote-control.md).

